"39:74:13" : {s: 39, a: 74, w: 13, r: "شيا", t: "نَشَآءُ", l: "شَآءَ", lc: 236, tl: "nashāu", lb: "ইচ্ছা করা",e: "we wish", b: "আমি চাইলে", f: 11, rm: "to will/wish. shaiun (pl. ashyaaun) - thing/matter, affair in any way, at all, what is willed or wished, aught, any extent. In direct objective case it is often used to denote the meaning a little, bit, at all. Adverbially it means in any way, at all."},
"39:74:14" : {s: 39, a: 74, w: 14, r: "نعم", t: "فَنِعْمَ", l: "نِعْمَ", lc: 17, tl: "faniʿ'ma", lb: "উত্তম, উৎকৃষ্ট",e: "So excellent", b: "কতইনা উত্তম", f: 5, rm: "to lead an easy life, enjoy the comforts and conveniences of life, be joyful, comforts/delights, become easy/soft/plentiful/pleasant/good/flourishing, to knead/cook well. inaam - beneficence, favour to a person, blessing, gifted (with speech/talent/reason etc)."},
